Witter & Witter Boston / Cape Cod Connection

description: Unique and architecturally interesting condo at the Macallen Building, Boston's first LEED gold certified building. Bathed in natural light with views towards Blue Hills and South End, this high-floor triplex offers 1,902 sqft with 2 beds, 2.5 baths, garage parking for 2 cars, plus a ~400 sqft private south-facing terrace with piped gas grill. High ceilings, contemporary finishes, and architecturally-inspired details define the home while a practical yet unique layout offers a departure from the expected. Many upgrades incl custom closets, lighting, AV, and more. Stellar location next to South End, Whole Foods, and only a short stroll down the Harbor Walk to the Seaport and Fort Point areas. For commuting, Mass Pike, I-93, and Broadway MBTA Station (Red Line) are located right outside the door. The Macallen is pet-friendly and offers 24/7 concierge, landscaped roof terrace with heated pool overlooking the city, gym, and screening room. Two full-size garage parking spaces included.
